We first extract the relevant fixed‐asset data. In the “Initial” part of the data the “Fixed Assets” row shows an amount of 8,000,000.00. (Other “Initial” rows such as cash and bank deposit do not affect fixed assets.) Then later a purchase of a fixed asset is recorded with the id “FixedAsset20231231001” for 251,793.02 (this row carries an “asset_name” and “asset_type” so it is a fixed‐asset purchase).

At period end the “net” fixed assets are computed as follows:

 • Initial fixed asset amount = 8,000,000.00  
 • Add: New fixed asset purchase = 251,793.02  
   Subtotal = 8,000,000.00 + 251,793.02 = 8,251,793.02  
 • Subtract: Accumulated depreciation  
  There are two “Depreciation” transactions:  
   – Depreciation20240101001 = 45,741.99  
   – Depreciation20240201002 = 50,737.35  
  Total Depreciation = 45,741.99 + 50,737.35 = 96,479.34  

Thus, the net fixed assets at period end are:  
  8,251,793.02 – 96,479.34 = 8,155,313.68

So the answers are:

 • Fixed assets net Initial Value: 8,000,000.00  
 • Fixed assets net End Value: 8,155,313.68
